hudson.model.BooleanParameterValue.name: RunCI
hudson.model.BooleanParameterValue.description: Untick will perform this Script verification Job ONLY and will not trigger the full performance test.

hudson.model.StringParameterValue.name: Application
hudson.model.StringParameterValue.description: Application name as it will appear in the Mark59 Trends application

hudson.model.StringParameterValue.name: Duration
hudson.model.StringParameterValue.description: Test run Duration in seconds - Should be only a long as necessary to validate the test plan

hudson.model.StringParameterValue.name: Users
hudson.model.StringParameterValue.description: Number of users to use for shakeout. Will be applied across all (non-metric) thread groups that have been parameterized.

hudson.model.StringParameterValue.name: MonitoringUsers
hudson.model.StringParameterValue.description: Number of users to use for shakeout of the 'metric capture' thread groups that have been parameterized (Usually either 1 or 0).

hudson.model.StringParameterValue.name: JmeterTestPlan
hudson.model.StringParameterValue.description: location of the test plan to execute

hudson.model.StringParameterValue.name: OverrideTestResultsFile
hudson.model.StringParameterValue.description: Jmeter results file location generally set to some temp location for verify, so as not to be confused with actual test

hudson.model.BooleanParameterValue.name: KillDrivers
hudson.model.BooleanParameterValue.description: Removes drives and browsers that may be left over from previous jobs (you may want to create separate jobs to Kill or not Kill drivers and browsers)

hudson.model.StringParameterValue.name: ExtraParam1
hudson.model.StringParameterValue.description:
ExtraParma1 - ExtraParam10 Available
Additional optional arguments that can be passed to Jmeter. For example, if your test plan has a parameter 'ForceTxnFailPercent' (sample usage : ${__P(ForceTxnFailPercent,25)} ), then a value can be passed from here such as:
-JForceTxnFailPercent=50

hudson.model.StringParameterValue.name: ExtraParam2
hudson.model.StringParameterValue.description: You can add all the 'ExtraParam' arguments in here if you wish , and leave there Default Values blank if they are not required

hudson.model.StringParameterValue.name: SetPath
hudson.model.StringParameterValue.description: the location of the Java version to use, and the wbem location. Used to invoke commands. wbem is required to run the WMIC commands used to capture Win metric data, and is not by default on the path.
